result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason D. Fraker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event probation is revoked, Defendant would be entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 3:04 p.m. Defendant Jason D. Fraker in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: NC. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. No statement by the defendant. Court orders: 45 days WCJ - Huber, GT, 1 day CFTS - I/S - 1 year probation - Conditions: AODA and follow through, defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.

3:16 pm case called. Defendant Jason D. Fraker in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Statement by Attorney Szilagyi requests matter be set for plea/sentencing in 30 days.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for February 1, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

Case Called @ 2:15 PM: Defendant Jason D. Fraker in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court questions Def as to status of counsel.  Def states he was not able to yet contact the SPD for eligibility.  Def again referred to SPD for completion of eligibility process.  STC again adjourned when Atty Szilagyi will be present.  Status conference scheduled for January 7, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

Case Called @ 1:47 PM: Defendant Jason D. Fraker in court, appearing in person due to severe hearing impairment.  Defendant Jason D. Fraker in court, in custody, appears via video.Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Prior to going of record, Def refused SPD services.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today and confirms he declined SPD representation.  Def wishes to plea guilty today.   Court undertakes colloquy and Def now requests counsel.  Court enters NGP.  Court orders $500 Signature Bond with Riverside determination.  Def again referred to SPD to complete eligibility.  Defendant to return by 2:30 PM today to meet with SPD.  Status conference scheduled for December 15, 2015 at 02:00 pm.
